## Dashboard Navigation Composition

Admin pages should not put every setting into one large form. Use `TxTabs` for first-level sections, `TxDropdownMenu` for lightweight actions in the current section, `TxPopover` for short explanations, and `TxDrawer` for dense configuration.

:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="ComponentsNavigationShellDemo" code-lang="vue" title="Dashboard navigation shell" description="A screenshot-verified Tabs / DropdownMenu / Popover / Drawer composition for Dashboard settings pages."}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const active = ref('Overview')
  const drawerVisible = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <section class="grid gap-3">
      <TxDropdownMenu>
        <template #trigger>
          <TxButton>Release actions</TxButton>
        </template>
        <TxDropdownItem>Quick release</TxDropdownItem>
      </TxDropdownMenu>

      <TxPopover>
        <template #reference>
          <TxButton variant="secondary">Policy notes</TxButton>
        </template>
        Keep popovers short and action-light.
      </TxPopover>

      <TxTabs v-model="active" placement="left" indicator-variant="pill">
        <TxTabItem name="Overview" activation>Overview settings</TxTabItem>
        <TxTabItem name="Releases">Release settings</TxTabItem>
      </TxTabs>

      <TxDrawer v-model:visible="drawerVisible" title="Release policy" />
    </section>
  </template>
---
:::

## API

### TxTabs Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|------|
| `modelValue` | `string` | - | Controlled active tab name. Prop-driven changes update the active panel without emitting `change`. |
| `defaultValue` | `string` | - | Initial uncontrolled active tab. It must match a `TxTabItem name`; otherwise no tab is selected. |
| `placement` | `'left' \| 'right' \| 'top' \| 'bottom'` | `'left'` | Navigation placement; invalid values fall back to `left`. |
| `offset` | `number` | `0` | Extra indicator offset along the active-tab axis for `line` / `pill` indicators. |
| `navMinWidth` | `number` | `220` | Minimum navigation width for vertical placements. |
| `navMaxWidth` | `number` | `320` | Maximum navigation width for vertical placements. |
| `contentPadding` | `number` | `12` | Padding applied to the main content panel. |
| `contentScrollable` | `boolean` | `true` | Wrap content in an internal scroll container; height animation disables the wrapper for direct measurement. |
| `borderless` | `boolean` | `false` | Remove the outer border and background for embedded layouts. |
| `autoHeight` | `boolean` | `false` | Enable AutoSizer height animation through the default `animation.size` configuration. |
| `autoWidth` | `boolean` | `false` | Enable AutoSizer width animation through the default `animation.size` configuration. |
| `showIndicator` | `boolean` | `true` | Render the animated active-tab pointer. Set to `false` for text-only navigation. |
| `indicatorVariant` | `'line' \| 'pill' \| 'block' \| 'dot' \| 'outline'` | `'line'` | Indicator style; invalid values fall back to `line`. |
| `indicatorMotion` | `'stretch' \| 'warp' \| 'glide' \| 'snap' \| 'spring'` | `'stretch'` | Indicator transition motion class; invalid values fall back to `stretch`. |
| `indicatorMotionStrength` | `number` | `1` | Non-negative CSS variable controlling indicator scale elasticity; negative values clamp to `0`. |
| `animation` | `TabsAnimation` | - | Per-area animation configuration for size, nav, indicator, and content transitions. |
| `animation.size` | `boolean \| { enabled?; durationMs?; easing? }` | derives from `autoHeight` / `autoWidth` | Enable and configure AutoSizer size animation; defaults to `autoHeightDurationMs` / `autoHeightEasing`. |
| `animation.nav` | `boolean \| { enabled?; durationMs?; easing? }` | enabled, `220ms ease` | Enable and configure nav width/layout transition variables. |
| `animation.indicator` | `boolean \| { enabled?; durationMs?; easing? }` | enabled, `350ms cubic-bezier(...)` | Enable and configure pointer position/size transitions. |
| `animation.content` | `boolean \| { enabled?; type?; durationMs?; durationRatio?; easing? }` | enabled `zoom`, `180ms ease` | Configure active-panel entry animation. `type` supports `fade`, `slide`, `zoom`, `blur`, `scale`, and `none`; `durationRatio` derives duration from indicator duration. |
| `autoHeightDurationMs` | `number` | `250` | Default size animation duration when `animation.size.durationMs` is omitted. |
| `autoHeightEasing` | `string` | `ease` | Default size animation easing when `animation.size.easing` is omitted. |

### TxTabs Events

| Event | Params | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `update:modelValue` | `value: string` | Emitted when user activation, `defaultValue`, or `activation` changes the active tab in uncontrolled flow. |
| `change` | `value: string` | Mirrors the same active tab name after activation. Prop-driven `modelValue` updates do not emit it. |

### TxTabs Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `default` | - | Provide direct `TxTabItem`, optional `TxTabItemGroup`, and optional `TxTabHeader` nodes. Fragments are unwrapped; unrelated nodes are ignored. |
| `nav-right` | - | Render compact controls at the end of the nav bar, commonly used for horizontal tabs. |

### TxTabs Exposed Methods

| Name | Type | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `refresh` | `() => void` | Forward to the internal AutoSizer `refresh()`. |
| `flip` | `(action: () => void \| Promise<void>) => Promise<void>` | Run an action inside the internal AutoSizer FLIP transition when available. |
| `action` | `(fn: (el: HTMLElement \| undefined) => void \| Promise<void>, optionsOrDetect?: any) => Promise<{ changedKeys: string[] } \| any>` | Forward to the internal AutoSizer action helper; falls back to calling `fn(undefined)`. |
| `size` | `() => { width: number; height: number } \| undefined` | Return the latest measured AutoSizer size. |

### TxTabItem Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|------|
| `name` | `string` | *required* | Unique tab name used as the active value and lookup key. |
| `iconClass` | `string` | `''` | Optional icon class rendered before the nav label. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Block click activation and render a disabled native button. |
| `activation` | `boolean` | `false` | Mark this tab as the uncontrolled default when neither `modelValue` nor `defaultValue` selects a tab. |

### TxTabItem Events

| Event | Params | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `click` | - | Emitted by standalone `TxTabItem` when not disabled; `TxTabs` consumes it to update active state. |

### TxTabItem Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `default` | - | Active panel content rendered by `TxTabs`. Inactive panels are not mounted. |
| `icon` | - | Custom navigation icon; replaces `iconClass`. |
| `name` | - | Custom navigation label; falls back to the `name` prop. |

### TxTabHeader Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|------|
| `node` | `unknown` | - | Active `TxTabItem` VNode passed by `TxTabs`; use `node?.props` defensively. |

### TxTabHeader Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `default` | `{ props: { node?: unknown } }` | Sticky content header rendered above the active panel. |

### TxTabItemGroup Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|------|
| `name` | `string` | - | Optional group label rendered in the navigation column. |

### TxTabItemGroup Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `default` | - | Child `TxTabItem` nodes. The group component itself renders no DOM outside `TxTabs`. |

## Interaction Contract

- `modelValue` is the controlled source. Parent-driven `modelValue` updates do not emit `change` or `update:modelValue` again.
- Without `modelValue`, `defaultValue` wins over `activation`. If `defaultValue` does not match a tab, `TxTabs` renders the empty state instead of falling back to `activation`.
- Only `TxTabItem`, `TxTabItemGroup`, and `TxTabHeader` nodes are collected from the default slot; fragments are supported, arbitrary wrappers are ignored.
- `TxTabItemGroup` is a navigation grouping marker; panel content still comes from each child `TxTabItem`.
- `showIndicator=false` removes the pointer DOM and pointer animation work. Size animation still observes content/nav when enabled.
- Height animation removes the internal scroll wrapper so AutoSizer can measure panel height directly; use `contentScrollable=false` for manual direct-measurement layouts.
- Inactive tab panels are not mounted. Store persistent panel state outside the panel subtree when it must survive switching.

## Style Customization

| Theme token / CSS variable | Used for |
|----------------------------|----------|
| `--tx-border-color` | Outer border and placement-specific nav divider. |
| `--tx-bg-color` | Tabs container background. |
| `--tx-fill-color` / `--tx-fill-color-light` | Active and hover nav item surfaces. |
| `--tx-color-primary` | Indicator gradient, glow, outline, and demo accent fills. |
| `--tx-text-color-primary` / `--tx-text-color-secondary` | Tab labels, icons, group labels, and empty-state text. |
| `--tx-tabs-indicator-duration` / `--tx-tabs-indicator-easing` / `--tx-tabs-indicator-strength` | Runtime variables generated from indicator animation props. |
| `--tx-tabs-content-duration` / `--tx-tabs-content-easing` | Runtime variables generated from content animation props. |
| `--tx-tabs-nav-duration` / `--tx-tabs-nav-easing` | Runtime variables generated from nav animation props. |

## Best Practices

- Keep `TxTabItem name` values stable, unique, and equal to the values used in `modelValue` / `defaultValue`.
- Prefer `placement="left"` for Dashboard settings and dense admin surfaces; use top/bottom tabs for short secondary switches.
- Use `defaultValue` only when the matching tab is guaranteed to exist. Use `activation` for static uncontrolled examples.
- Do not put long-lived form state only inside inactive panels; inactive tab content is unmounted during switches.
- For panels whose height changes after async data or image load, combine direct measurement (`contentScrollable=false` or `autoHeight`) with `refresh()` after the content settles.
- Keep `nav-right` compact. Move dense actions into `TxDropdownMenu`, `TxPopover`, or `TxDrawer` instead of growing the tab bar.

## Review Notes

- Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/tabs/src/TxTabs.vue`, `TxTabItem.vue`, `TxTabHeader.vue`, `TxTabItemGroup.vue`, and `types.ts`.
- `indicatorMotionStrength` is a runtime prop on `TxTabs` and is now present in the exported `TabsProps` interface.
- `TxTabItemGroup.vue` intentionally renders an empty template; `TxTabs` reads its child `TxTabItem` VNodes and creates the group DOM.
- `TxTabs` filters the default slot by component name, so docs should not show arbitrary wrapper components around tab items.

